sudo lspci


Steps to install git :
...................................
1. sudo apt-get install git
2. git config –global user.name “your_username”
3. git config –global user.email “your_emailid”
4. mkdir myproject
5 .cd myproject
6 git init
7 git remote add origin  https://github.com/your_username/myproject.git
8 git add helloworld.c  or git add . (for more then one file)
9 git commit -m ‘your_message’
10 git push origin master  (push the changes and to see what is pushed)

done 

to pull the changes 

11. git pull origin master


